10/03/2011
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Interior Minister Traian Igas announced on Wednesday (March 9th) that about 9,000 jobs in his ministry will be slashed this year to boost efficiency and crack down on corruption.
The first to go will be incompetent employees and those under criminal investigation.
There are 160,000 people working for the interior ministry at the moment.
(Realitatea, Evenimentul Zilei, Antean 3, Gandul - 09/03/11)
